    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nYes, Vim 8.2.3288 for `vim.g.*`\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\n`vim._setvar()` and `nvim_set_var` currently allow assigning a Lua function to a global lowercase Vim variable. However, according to `:h Funcref`:\r\n```\r\nA Funcref variable must start with a capital, \"s:\", \"w:\", \"t:\" or \"b:\".  You\r\ncan use \"g:\" but the following name must still start with a capital.  You\r\ncannot have both a Funcref variable and a function with the same name.\r\n```\r\nSo assigning a Lua function to a global lowercase Vim variable should not be allowed for consistency.",
